Rucola is wonderful! This place has become a Boerum Hill staple, and continually earns itself the title of 'Best Restaurant in Boerum Hill" in my book. You've likely done the research prior to reading this post, but if you don't know, it's Italian cuisine, farm-to-table, and not that large of a space - though, it has a very cute, quaint and rustic decor. I've been there a dozen or so times, and it's never not been packed - but it feels more cozy than anything else, which is impressive, because you can be extremely close to the table next to you. Absolutely plan ahead and make reservations, because you will have a 0.001% chance of getting a table as a walk-up... that's true for weekdays as well as weekends.

3.5 stars... This is a tough one because some parts of the experience were great. The whitefish crostini with avocado, lemon, radish and cucumber was good, the campanelle pasta with artichokes, capers, and parmesan was also good as was the short rib with celery root puree and mushrooms, but the olive oil chocolate pudding with sea salt was great. The taste of everything we ate was delicious. ...but... 1) the kitchen was slow, we waited an hour for our main course, 2) the dinner plates were not dinner sized portions but were priced at double the appetizer price (example the 'dinner' short rib portion was literally six bites....), and finally 3) the place was loud and crowded and not very spacious. I'm not saying it's a fire hazard but so many tables are crammed in it'd be hard to escape. This place might be fabulous off-peak when it's not crowded. That's when I would go again.

Unfortunately, I will never again eat here. The service we received last night was atrocious.  We arrived as a walk-in (no reservation) before the dinner rush, there were three of us, and were immediately seated at a table. As soon as we sat, the hostess came back over to us and explained that the couple who had just walked in were a table of four, she asked us to move to the communal table. Generally, I would be put off by this, but we were happy to accommodate, though it was kind of tactless.  However, when we sat at the communal table, over the next 15 min we were ignored by everyone in the restaurant. The couple who was given our original table received water, they made a wine selection, received bread AND their wine... AND ordered and received an appetizer before anyone even acknowledged our presence (and I want to note the second half of their party didn't arrive for another 20 minutes). I was literally making note of all of this after I became more and more upset.  During this period, they were setting the communal table for a big group. While we were sitting and waiting, a server dropped bottles of water for the expected group at the table (none of which had shown up at this point) my husband stood up and grabbed a bottle of water that was set out on the table, this because in the 15 min wait, none had bothered to bring us water. When the waiter noticed my husband doing this, he glared annoyingly at us and aggressively replaced the bottle of water. I was absolutely shocked.  We were about to walk out when a server finally came over at about 18 min of waiting, and took our drink orders. It was at this time the large group started to arrive. The restaurant immediately became so crowded that the servers had to inch their way behind me to work and they were constantly hitting my arms and back. We received our drinks as my husband tried to tell the server that we were ready to order, they had rushed off again, and waited for another 7 min... before they came back around. Still no bread, and the bottle of water we had acquired on our own was long gone.  At this point we were so upset, we decided to leave. My husband talked to the waiter about all this, and asked for the check... not one apology, nothing. Even the hostess ignored us and our obvious dissatisfaction with the way we were treated.  Listen, their food may be good but the service is horrendous, there are so many gems in this neighborhood that treat their customers like family. It's a shame this place misses the boat. Final warning: avoid Rucola it's just not a cool place.

OVERPRICED & OVERRATED COZY PLACE.  Honestly I don’t know why this place has such as great rating considering the food.  ENVIRONMENT Very nice. They used an old house and decorated every single inch of it and made it feel like one of the coziest places you’ve ever been.  SEATING is COMPLICATED. My friend Phil called in advance asking for a table for 3. When we arrived we learned we had to share a long table with 17 more people... Which is not a problem but definitely not what you expect when you have a RESERVATION.  FOOD IS AVERAGE For appetizers we ordered the “Chef’s Selection of Cheese, Meat and Vegetables” ($22 USD). The chef chose for us Spicy ‘Nduja,  Prosciutto San Daniele, Moses Sleeper and Comte cheeses as well as Marinated Olives and Pickled Fennel. Amongst all 3 of us only ate half of that because IT WAS NOT GOOD.  For my salad I chose the Radicchio & Endive SALAD ($12) that comes with walnuts and Gorgonzola cheese. That was an GOOD choice. They add some orange to it and it makes a great combination for a salad and the ingredients tasted fresh.  For the entree I chose the Whole Roasted Brook Trout. The fish was too salty, although the presentation was good.  SERVICE IS MEDIOCRE. The waiters seems anxious to get us eating, wouldn’t let us have a peaceful conversation without interruptions such as “Are you ready yet?” “Need more time?” “A few more minutes?”. Ugh. Top this off with lack of smiles or wit that you’ll find in any modern restaurant today... Even in Starbucks!  NOT ALL WINES Also, what type of fancy restaurant doesn’t have all the wine they show you in their menu?  PRICE For 3 people having a bottle of mediocre wine, average food and Ok dessert, mediocre service and paying $250 seems EXPENSIVE for what you get.

Will be back again for those scallops too and the TRUFFLES!
Great food great staff wonderful experience
Always crowded

Amazing neighborhood gem! The food here is so fantastic - everything is very fresh and homemade. The vegetables available as antipasti are incredibly tasty. We loved the pasta too. Suggest getting here early for dinner - they don't take reservations unless you have a party of 5 or more and it does get busy!
Very quaint Italian restaurant. And while the menu is quite limited everything on it is made very well. Cocktails are also very tasty.

It is a tiny restaurant and was full when me and my wife were there yesterday. The tables are so close to each other that it´s like you are sharing one big table with everybody else. It didn´t bother us. The place is pleasant, the service is excellent and the food is great, despite the menu has quite few options. The cheese plate is awesome, we had a great Pinot Noir and the dessert was good, too. Would definitely recommend!
Fabulous food and by far the best arugula salad I've had.  Plan ahead, smaller place fills up fast.  Cozy neighborhood eats.
Delicious food, well rounded Italian wine, cozy ambiance

A hidden gem in Boerum Hill! I would have never been able to find this place without Yelp but I'm glad I did. The restaurant is small but when you walk in you feel like your in a old Italian wine cellar, almost underground in a way. It made the dining experience all the better. The menu is short and simple, we ordered the lumache pasta and flank steak. There is nothing worse then over cooked pasta but not here! The pasta was cooked perfectly and each piece of pasta was coated in the delicious sauce, I could eat a shoe coated in the sauce. The flank steak was cooked to a perfect medium rare, my girlfriend refuses to eat bloody meat and she enjoyed this steak. The meat was done perfectly without leaking too much blood. It was a delicious and hearty dinner. We will definitely be coming back for more!

Definitely need a reservation. Excellent food. Nice service. It’s actually great for breakfast too - much quieter. It’s a nice place to start your day. Night can feel crowded and loud but it’s lovely. I had chicken and it was delicious.
Nice breakfast. Small plates. Lovely interior.
Great breakfast
Cool atmosphere, great food, exceptional service. And the salted caramel apple pie was just amazing :)
Such a consistently great, cozy restaurant. Perfect for small celebrations or just a fun, beautiful dinner.
You're guaranteed to have a lovely time at this quaint neighborhood restaurant
Good food and service

I think this may have been the best meal of my life. The chickpea purée was unspeakably good, as was everything else I tried (chicken, burata, and chocolate pudding). Also, it's a super cute place with a great energy. Seriously, don't miss this place!
One of my favorite places for great steaks and pasta. A tiny bit expensive.

I wish I could give this place 4.5 stars, but oh well - erring on the side of "incredibly high expectations were not met".  On any given night the wait could be hours, depending on when you arrive.  They don't take reservations, which I personally find frustrating.  So when we finally got a table, expectations were through the roof!  Service was excellent (waiter was a Jon Hamm look-alike).  Food was excellent, too.  I guess the thing is: when you wait 2 hours for a table, you expect to have your mind blown, and well - it just wasn't.

Never had a bad dish here, and the cocktails are thoughtful and subtle. It's always crowded, which is a bummer, but if you just plan ahead, or go at an of hour, you can have a delightful meal. Prices are quite reasonable for the quality.
House made pasta, nuanced sauces. Everything about the meal was beyond our expectations.

Went there last night before a concert at the Barclay's Center. We arrived at 4:30 which gave us enough time to investigate the wonderful menu! Dinner began at 5:30. If you're looking for AUTHENTIC northern Italian cuisine, look no further! The trout melts in your mouth! That appetizers are right out of Italy! This place is rustic, cozy, and the staff is friendly and attentive. Order a bottle of wine and enjoy! My Sicilian wife and will definitely be back!
Great atmosphere and good food. Came here for breakfast.
The Brooklyn version of Cafe Cluny. Always a celebrity on site. The food is very good, service depends but is definitely on the better side. Interior is very cozy.
Really delicious, beautiful restaurant.
The most consistently excellent restaurant in the neighborhood.  Fail safe.

Met an old friend here for dinner on a Monday night. We showed up just in time (7pm), because by 7:20 the place was packed. Wonderful, veggie and fresh pasta forward menu. The lamb ragu was fantastic and I would strongly recommend this place to anyone (unless they like lots of personal space).

Loved that this place was open early for brunch! Beautiful spot in the neighborhood . The sandwich I had was fantastic - delicious bread and very fresh, simple authentic ingredients. The coffee was good as well. Would definitely recommend and return to try the rest of their menu!
Good, fresh ingredients. Bomb bread. Don't bother with dessert. Good wine.  Weird vibe.. waitstaff made us felt like we were intruding.
Fantastic, carefully selected menu and friendly, generous staff. Felt like I was back in Italy!
Tasty Italian cuisine and great cocktail.

Great neighborhood spot. Limited menu but everything delicious. Had the chicken - great salty, crispy skin - cooked perfectly. Cold refreshing squash blossom app. Creamy polenta pesto side. Top notch.
